'''Yazan Mousa Mahmoud Abu Al-Arab''' ({{langx|ar|يَزَن مُوسَى مَحْمُود أَبُو الْعَرَب}}; born 31 January 1996) is a Jordanian professional footballer who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[K-League]] side [[FC Seoul]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Club career==
===Selangor===
On 18 December 2021, Yazan officially signed up with [[Malaysia Super League]] club, [[Selangor F.C.|Selangor]] alongside national teammate [[Baha' Abdel-Rahman]] for 2022 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://selangorfc.com/ms/news/3107/OFFICIAL%20%20%20Yazan%20Al-Arab%20Is%20RED! |title=RASMI : Yazan Al-Arab Is RED! |date=17 December 2021 |access-date=17 December 2021 |work=selangorfc.com |publisher=Selangor FC}}</ref>

On 3 October 2023, his contract was officially terminated by Selangor FC following an on-field incident involving a match official in a Malaysia Cup match against Terengganu FC on 24 September 2023.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.vocketfc.com/terkini-selangor-rasmi-tamatkan-kontrak-yazan-al-arab-yang-sepak-pengadil/|title=TERKINI: Selangor Rasmi Tamatkan Kontrak Yazan Al Arab Yang Sepak Pengadil |website=vocketfc.com |publisher=Vocket FC |date=3 October 2023 |access-date=3 October 2023 |author=Axello }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bharian.com.my/sukan/bola/2023/10/1160365/selangor-tamatkan-kontrak-yazan |title=Selangor tamatkan kontrak Yazan |work=bharian.com.my |publisher=Berita Harian |date=3 October 2023 |access-date=3 October 2023 |first=Zulfaizan |last=Mansor}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hmetro.com.my/arena/bola-sepak/2023/10/1016125/selangor-tamat-kontrak-yazan |title=Selangor tamat kontrak Yazan |work=hmetro.com.my |publisher=Harian Metro |date=3 October 2023 |access-date=3 October 2023 |first=Firdaus |last=Hashim}}</ref>

On 20 November 2023, Yazan has been banned for life from Malaysian football. The [[Football Association of Malaysia]] gave a lifetime ban because he violated Article 51, paragraph 1(a) and Article 59 of the association's Disciplinary Code but said the decision could be appealed.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.https/ |title=Jordanian centreback Yazan Al-Arab banned from Malaysian football after referee assault |work=thestar.com.my |publisher=The Star |date=20 November 2023 |access-date=29 November 2023 |first=T |last=Avineshawaran |archive-date=19 August 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130819141428/http://https/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

===FC Seoul===
In July 2024, Yazan signed with [[FC Seoul]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Hwang|first=Min-kuk|script-title=ko:FC서울, 요르단 국가대표 수비수 알아랍 영입|url=https://sports.khan.co.kr/sports/sk_index.html?art_id=202407161215003|website=[[Sports Kyunghyang]]|publisher=Kyunghyang Company|access-date=16 July 2024|language=ko|date=16 July 2024}}</ref> He was named as a candidate for [[2024 K League 1|K League]]'s Player of the Month award for the month of August in 2024,<ref>{{cite web |title=이달의선수상 8월 후보 야잔, 이승모 |url=https://www.instagram.com/fcseoul/p/C_egW4ZyB1A/?hl=en&img_index=1 |website=Instagram.com |publisher=FC Seoul |access-date=14 September 2024 |language=Korean |date=3 September 2024}}</ref> making an immediate impression for the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=يزن العرب حديث الشارع الكوري |url=https://jfranews.com.jo/article/466093 |website=jfranews |publisher=Jfra News |access-date=14 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=27 August 2024}}</ref> In July 2025 Yazan scored against Spanish giant [[FC Barcelona]] during a [[friendly match]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Roberts |first=Mike |date=31 July 2025 |title=FC Seoul 3–7 FC Barcelona: Goalfest in Korea |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/4329645/fc-seoul-37-fc-barcelona-goalfest-in-korea |website=[[FC Barcelona]]}}</ref>

== International career ==
Al-Arab has been a regular for the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]] since 2017.

